<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-192] Lustre manual doesn&apos;t open in some browsers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-192</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On IE 8 for Dan Cobb. On Firefox for Linda Bebernes. Other browsers not tested.&lt;br/&gt;
(Linda) When an attempt is made to open the xhtml version of the Lustre manual in Firefox, an error message is displayed:&lt;br/&gt;
XML Parsing Error: mismatched tag. Expected: &amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;. Location: &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.xhtml&lt;/a&gt; Line Number 532, Column 873: more details about OSS failover, see &amp;lt;a class=&quot;xref&quot; href=&quot;#understandingfailover&quot; title=&quot;Chapter 3. Understanding Failover in Lustre&quot;&amp;gt;Chapter 3, &amp;lt;em&amp;gt;Understanding Failover in Lustre&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div class=&quot;figure&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;a id=&quot;idp664848&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p class=&quot;title&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;Figure 1.2. &amp;lt;a id=&quot;idp665712&quot; class=&quot;indexterm&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;Lustre* cluster at scale&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div class=&quot;figure-contents&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div class=&quot;mediaobject&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;table border=&quot;0&quot; summary=&quot;manufactured viewport for HTML img&quot; style=&quot;cellpadding: 0; cellspacing: 0;&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;tr&amp;gt;&amp;lt;td&amp;gt;&amp;lt;img src=&quot;./figures/Scaled_Cluster.png&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; alt=&quot;Lustre* clustre at scale&quot; /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/tr&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/table&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br class=&quot;figure-break&quot; /&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div class=&quot;titlepage&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h2 class=&quot;title&quot; style=&quot;clear: both&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;a id=&quot;understandinglustre.storageio&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;1.3 id=&quot;idp670864&quot; class=&quot;indexterm&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Linda) When an attempt is made to open the PDF in firefox, the PDF frame appears but no TOC or content.&lt;br/&gt;
-----------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Dan) When an attempt is made to open the xhtml file in IE 8, an &quot;unknown file type&quot; error message is displayed.   [the xhtml file opens in Linda&apos;s IE 8 browser)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-------------&lt;br/&gt;
(Dan) When an attempt is made to open the PDF in IE8, it doesn&apos;t load. (It loads fine in Linda&apos;s IE 8 browser).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
